{
  "@context": "http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json",
  "id": "https://tanyaclement.github.io/harvard1953/annotations/august-5-evening-part-two-canvas-1-frank-o-connor.json",
  "type": "AnnotationPage",
  "label": "Frank O'Connor",
  "items": [
    {
      "@context": "http://www.w3.org/ns/anno.jsonld",
      "id": "august-5-evening-part-two-canvas-1-frank-o-connor-annotation-0.json",
      "type": "Annotation",
      "motivation": [
        "supplementing",
        "commenting"
      ],
      "body": [
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "value": " I don't know that I have very much to say. And I'm very much afraid of saying what I have to say because it puts me into a state of permanent opposition. And that's a state I don't want to get into, particularly as my relations with publishers and agents have always been remarkably good.",
          "format": "text/plain",
          "purpose": "commenting"
        },
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "value": "Frank O'Connor",
          "format": "text/plain",
          "purpose": "tagging"
        },
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "value": "August 5 Panel Dicussion",
          "format": "text/plain",
          "purpose": "tagging"
        }
      ],
      "target": {
        "source": {
          "id": "https://tanyaclement.github.io/harvard1953/august-5-evening-part-two/canvas-1/canvas",
          "type": "Canvas",
          "partOf": [
            {
              "id": "https://tanyaclement.github.io/harvard1953/august-5-evening-part-two/manifest.json",
              "type": "Manifest"
            }
          ]
        },
        "selector": {
          "type": "PointSelector",
          "t": "212.0"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "@context": "http://www.w3.org/ns/anno.jsonld",
      "id": "august-5-evening-part-two-canvas-1-frank-o-connor-annotation-1.json",
      "type": "Annotation",
      "motivation": [
        "supplementing",
        "commenting"
      ],
      "body": [
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "value": " And in fact, the only advice I ever give young writers is, find a good publisher and find a good agent and stick to them for the Lord sake. Don't go wandering around. I think I was frightfully alarmed by Miss Livingstone's speech.",
          "format": "text/plain",
          "purpose": "commenting"
        },
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "value": "Frank O'Connor",
          "format": "text/plain",
          "purpose": "tagging"
        },
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "value": "August 5 Panel Dicussion",
          "format": "text/plain",
          "purpose": "tagging"
        }
      ],
      "target": {
        "source": {
          "id": "https://tanyaclement.github.io/harvard1953/august-5-evening-part-two/canvas-1/canvas",
          "type": "Canvas",
          "partOf": [
            {
              "id": "https://tanyaclement.github.io/harvard1953/august-5-evening-part-two/manifest.json",
              "type": "Manifest"
            }
          ]
        },
        "selector": {
          "type": "PointSelector",
          "t": "237.0"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "@context": "http://www.w3.org/ns/anno.jsonld",
      "id": "august-5-evening-part-two-canvas-1-frank-o-connor-annotation-2.json",
      "type": "Annotation",
      "motivation": [
        "supplementing",
        "commenting"
      ],
      "body": [
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "value": " I know it all sounds wonderful. Here is Faulkner by the 6 million. You're spreading the lies on a scale in which the light has never been spread before. Now, I'm a great believer, as you've gathered, in getting an audience for literature and in showing respect for one's audience.",
          "format": "text/plain",
          "purpose": "commenting"
        },
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "value": "Frank O'Connor",
          "format": "text/plain",
          "purpose": "tagging"
        },
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "value": "August 5 Panel Dicussion",
          "format": "text/plain",
          "purpose": "tagging"
        }
      ],
      "target": {
        "source": {
          "id": "https://tanyaclement.github.io/harvard1953/august-5-evening-part-two/canvas-1/canvas",
          "type": "Canvas",
          "partOf": [
            {
              "id": "https://tanyaclement.github.io/harvard1953/august-5-evening-part-two/manifest.json",
              "type": "Manifest"
            }
          ]
        },
        "selector": {
          "type": "PointSelector",
          "t": "259.0"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "@context": "http://www.w3.org/ns/anno.jsonld",
      "id": "august-5-evening-part-two-canvas-1-frank-o-connor-annotation-3.json",
      "type": "Annotation",
      "motivation": [
        "supplementing",
        "commenting"
      ],
      "body": [
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "value": " The moment you begin to talk to me about an audience of 6 million, I want to run. Remember, I realize perfectly well that Miss Livingstone is full of almost a starry-eyed idealism about this. But there are a number of wicked people in the world who will not have her idealism.",
          "format": "text/plain",
          "purpose": "commenting"
        },
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "value": "Frank O'Connor",
          "format": "text/plain",
          "purpose": "tagging"
        },
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "value": "August 5 Panel Dicussion",
          "format": "text/plain",
          "purpose": "tagging"
        }
      ],
      "target": {
        "source": {
          "id": "https://tanyaclement.github.io/harvard1953/august-5-evening-part-two/canvas-1/canvas",
          "type": "Canvas",
          "partOf": [
            {
              "id": "https://tanyaclement.github.io/harvard1953/august-5-evening-part-two/manifest.json",
              "type": "Manifest"
            }
          ]
        },
        "selector": {
          "type": "PointSelector",
          "t": "286.0"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "@context": "http://www.w3.org/ns/anno.jsonld",
      "id": "august-5-evening-part-two-canvas-1-frank-o-connor-annotation-4.json",
      "type": "Annotation",
      "motivation": [
        "supplementing",
        "commenting"
      ],
      "body": [
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "value": " And that sort of attitude towards literature is not entirely new because in fact, it was the gospel of somebody who was anything but a starry-eyed idealist. And that was Lord Northcliffe, who valorized the English press out of existence.",
          "format": "text/plain",
          "purpose": "commenting"
        },
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "value": "Frank O'Connor",
          "format": "text/plain",
          "purpose": "tagging"
        },
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "value": "August 5 Panel Dicussion",
          "format": "text/plain",
          "purpose": "tagging"
        }
      ],
      "target": {
        "source": {
          "id": "https://tanyaclement.github.io/harvard1953/august-5-evening-part-two/canvas-1/canvas",
          "type": "Canvas",
          "partOf": [
            {
              "id": "https://tanyaclement.github.io/harvard1953/august-5-evening-part-two/manifest.json",
              "type": "Manifest"
            }
          ]
        },
        "selector": {
          "type": "PointSelector",
          "t": "310.0"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "@context": "http://www.w3.org/ns/anno.jsonld",
      "id": "august-5-evening-part-two-canvas-1-frank-o-connor-annotation-5.json",
      "type": "Annotation",
      "motivation": [
        "supplementing",
        "commenting"
      ],
      "body": [
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "value": " Remember the moment money comes into business on that scale, art begins to go out. I can hear Monsieur Simenon side beside me. I know he doesn't agree with me. But I've had some experience of this in the theater. And the thing which Mr. Sloan said is the real secret of it, that publishing in the 19th century was a smaller operation.",
          "format": "text/plain",
          "purpose": "commenting"
        },
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "value": "Frank O'Connor",
          "format": "text/plain",
          "purpose": "tagging"
        },
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "value": "August 5 Panel Dicussion",
          "format": "text/plain",
          "purpose": "tagging"
        }
      ],
      "target": {
        "source": {
          "id": "https://tanyaclement.github.io/harvard1953/august-5-evening-part-two/canvas-1/canvas",
          "type": "Canvas",
          "partOf": [
            {
              "id": "https://tanyaclement.github.io/harvard1953/august-5-evening-part-two/manifest.json",
              "type": "Manifest"
            }
          ]
        },
        "selector": {
          "type": "PointSelector",
          "t": "332.0"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "@context": "http://www.w3.org/ns/anno.jsonld",
      "id": "august-5-evening-part-two-canvas-1-frank-o-connor-annotation-6.json",
      "type": "Annotation",
      "motivation": [
        "supplementing",
        "commenting"
      ],
      "body": [
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "value": " And you realize that when you've worked in a theater, real theater like the Abay, that a problem of capitalisation becomes a very serious one. I realized that I could produce any play for 100 pounds, $300. And consequently, every young writer got a chance.",
          "format": "text/plain",
          "purpose": "commenting"
        },
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "value": "Frank O'Connor",
          "format": "text/plain",
          "purpose": "tagging"
        },
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "value": "August 5 Panel Dicussion",
          "format": "text/plain",
          "purpose": "tagging"
        }
      ],
      "target": {
        "source": {
          "id": "https://tanyaclement.github.io/harvard1953/august-5-evening-part-two/canvas-1/canvas",
          "type": "Canvas",
          "partOf": [
            {
              "id": "https://tanyaclement.github.io/harvard1953/august-5-evening-part-two/manifest.json",
              "type": "Manifest"
            }
          ]
        },
        "selector": {
          "type": "PointSelector",
          "t": "365.0"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "@context": "http://www.w3.org/ns/anno.jsonld",
      "id": "august-5-evening-part-two-canvas-1-frank-o-connor-annotation-7.json",
      "type": "Annotation",
      "motivation": [
        "supplementing",
        "commenting"
      ],
      "body": [
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "value": " And I'm quite certain, speaking as a man who has been director of a theater, that William Shakespeare's Henry V cost his company about $300, the most, $500 to produce. And the famous Hamlet that we saw cost $3 million to produce.",
          "format": "text/plain",
          "purpose": "commenting"
        },
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "value": "Frank O'Connor",
          "format": "text/plain",
          "purpose": "tagging"
        },
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "value": "August 5 Panel Dicussion",
          "format": "text/plain",
          "purpose": "tagging"
        }
      ],
      "target": {
        "source": {
          "id": "https://tanyaclement.github.io/harvard1953/august-5-evening-part-two/canvas-1/canvas",
          "type": "Canvas",
          "partOf": [
            {
              "id": "https://tanyaclement.github.io/harvard1953/august-5-evening-part-two/manifest.json",
              "type": "Manifest"
            }
          ]
        },
        "selector": {
          "type": "PointSelector",
          "t": "393.0"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "@context": "http://www.w3.org/ns/anno.jsonld",
      "id": "august-5-evening-part-two-canvas-1-frank-o-connor-annotation-8.json",
      "type": "Annotation",
      "motivation": [
        "supplementing",
        "commenting"
      ],
      "body": [
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "value": " Now the difference between the screen Hamlet and the theater Hamlet was that Shakespeare didn't have to worry about what he said. That beautiful scene in which the French officers speak, tell dirty stories, has just disappeared. So much capital has gone in. And I've worked on films as well as working in the theater. And I realized that the more capital you put into anything, the more people come along and say, oh, you can't say this. There's too much money involved in this.",
          "format": "text/plain",
          "purpose": "commenting"
        },
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "value": "Frank O'Connor",
          "format": "text/plain",
          "purpose": "tagging"
        },
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "value": "August 5 Panel Dicussion",
          "format": "text/plain",
          "purpose": "tagging"
        }
      ],
      "target": {
        "source": {
          "id": "https://tanyaclement.github.io/harvard1953/august-5-evening-part-two/canvas-1/canvas",
          "type": "Canvas",
          "partOf": [
            {
              "id": "https://tanyaclement.github.io/harvard1953/august-5-evening-part-two/manifest.json",
              "type": "Manifest"
            }
          ]
        },
        "selector": {
          "type": "PointSelector",
          "t": "420.0"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "@context": "http://www.w3.org/ns/anno.jsonld",
      "id": "august-5-evening-part-two-canvas-1-frank-o-connor-annotation-9.json",
      "type": "Annotation",
      "motivation": [
        "supplementing",
        "commenting"
      ],
      "body": [
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "value": " And I much prefer the smaller operation. Also when you get over-capitalization, don't forget that the squeeze is put on from other directions in the cinema. The squeeze is being put on by the workers as well. The industry has to pay out huge salaries. And the writers have to produce for the huge salaries.",
          "format": "text/plain",
          "purpose": "commenting"
        },
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "value": "Frank O'Connor",
          "format": "text/plain",
          "purpose": "tagging"
        },
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "value": "August 5 Panel Dicussion",
          "format": "text/plain",
          "purpose": "tagging"
        }
      ],
      "target": {
        "source": {
          "id": "https://tanyaclement.github.io/harvard1953/august-5-evening-part-two/canvas-1/canvas",
          "type": "Canvas",
          "partOf": [
            {
              "id": "https://tanyaclement.github.io/harvard1953/august-5-evening-part-two/manifest.json",
              "type": "Manifest"
            }
          ]
        },
        "selector": {
          "type": "PointSelector",
          "t": "453.0"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "@context": "http://www.w3.org/ns/anno.jsonld",
      "id": "august-5-evening-part-two-canvas-1-frank-o-connor-annotation-10.json",
      "type": "Annotation",
      "motivation": [
        "supplementing",
        "commenting"
      ],
      "body": [
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "value": " They've got to produce happy endings. It's just too bad. But happy endings are necessary. And the pressure gets more and more extreme. I firmly believe that you cannot have an art if publishing is going to be over-capitalized. I want to see books produced in reasonable editions. And I want them to see them produced as cheaply as possible.",
          "format": "text/plain",
          "purpose": "commenting"
        },
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "value": "Frank O'Connor",
          "format": "text/plain",
          "purpose": "tagging"
        },
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "value": "August 5 Panel Dicussion",
          "format": "text/plain",
          "purpose": "tagging"
        }
      ],
      "target": {
        "source": {
          "id": "https://tanyaclement.github.io/harvard1953/august-5-evening-part-two/canvas-1/canvas",
          "type": "Canvas",
          "partOf": [
            {
              "id": "https://tanyaclement.github.io/harvard1953/august-5-evening-part-two/manifest.json",
              "type": "Manifest"
            }
          ]
        },
        "selector": {
          "type": "PointSelector",
          "t": "481.0"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "@context": "http://www.w3.org/ns/anno.jsonld",
      "id": "august-5-evening-part-two-canvas-1-frank-o-connor-annotation-11.json",
      "type": "Annotation",
      "motivation": [
        "supplementing",
        "commenting"
      ],
      "body": [
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "value": " I do not want to have to cater for a public of 200,000 or 500,000, not because I don't respect them as much as I respect my own public of 3,000 or 4,000. I respect them every bit as much. But I know that if I attempt to reach them, I'm going to be destroyed as a writer.",
          "format": "text/plain",
          "purpose": "commenting"
        },
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "value": "Frank O'Connor",
          "format": "text/plain",
          "purpose": "tagging"
        },
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "value": "August 5 Panel Dicussion",
          "format": "text/plain",
          "purpose": "tagging"
        }
      ],
      "target": {
        "source": {
          "id": "https://tanyaclement.github.io/harvard1953/august-5-evening-part-two/canvas-1/canvas",
          "type": "Canvas",
          "partOf": [
            {
              "id": "https://tanyaclement.github.io/harvard1953/august-5-evening-part-two/manifest.json",
              "type": "Manifest"
            }
          ]
        },
        "selector": {
          "type": "PointSelector",
          "t": "506.0"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "@context": "http://www.w3.org/ns/anno.jsonld",
      "id": "august-5-evening-part-two-canvas-1-frank-o-connor-annotation-12.json",
      "type": "Annotation",
      "motivation": [
        "supplementing",
        "commenting"
      ],
      "body": [
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "value": " Also another thing I'm very much afraid of about these Pocket Books, I've seen it happen in England. Miss Livingstone described the work of the reprint editor, the reprint editor, with these figures in his head, is going to choose, perhaps in a most idealistic way, perhaps in a not very idealistic way, but it's already beginning to create an awful amount of mischief in England because you get the general idea, if this book is any good, it's going to appear in a pocket edition within a year.",
          "format": "text/plain",
          "purpose": "commenting"
        },
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "value": "Frank O'Connor",
          "format": "text/plain",
          "purpose": "tagging"
        },
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "value": "August 5 Panel Dicussion",
          "format": "text/plain",
          "purpose": "tagging"
        }
      ],
      "target": {
        "source": {
          "id": "https://tanyaclement.github.io/harvard1953/august-5-evening-part-two/canvas-1/canvas",
          "type": "Canvas",
          "partOf": [
            {
              "id": "https://tanyaclement.github.io/harvard1953/august-5-evening-part-two/manifest.json",
              "type": "Manifest"
            }
          ]
        },
        "selector": {
          "type": "PointSelector",
          "t": "534.0"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "@context": "http://www.w3.org/ns/anno.jsonld",
      "id": "august-5-evening-part-two-canvas-1-frank-o-connor-annotation-13.json",
      "type": "Annotation",
      "motivation": [
        "supplementing",
        "commenting"
      ],
      "body": [
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "value": " The fact that an author, and here, I am not speaking-- I shouldn't be speaking really at all because I'm involved in the matter. You get the feeling that any author who doesn't get into the Pocket Books can't be a really good author. And it's creating a new vulgarity, I think, in literature, a new snobbishness of sales.",
          "format": "text/plain",
          "purpose": "commenting"
        },
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "value": "Frank O'Connor",
          "format": "text/plain",
          "purpose": "tagging"
        },
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "value": "August 5 Panel Dicussion",
          "format": "text/plain",
          "purpose": "tagging"
        }
      ],
      "target": {
        "source": {
          "id": "https://tanyaclement.github.io/harvard1953/august-5-evening-part-two/canvas-1/canvas",
          "type": "Canvas",
          "partOf": [
            {
              "id": "https://tanyaclement.github.io/harvard1953/august-5-evening-part-two/manifest.json",
              "type": "Manifest"
            }
          ]
        },
        "selector": {
          "type": "PointSelector",
          "t": "574.0"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "@context": "http://www.w3.org/ns/anno.jsonld",
      "id": "august-5-evening-part-two-canvas-1-frank-o-connor-annotation-14.json",
      "type": "Annotation",
      "motivation": [
        "supplementing",
        "commenting"
      ],
      "body": [
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "value": " We're beginning to lose the old respect for the job as a job, whether it sells or whether it doesn't sell. And all I'll say is I know perfectly well Mr. Sloan and Ms Livingstone share my views on this. And would prefer a fine book which only sold 1,000 copies to a really bad book that sold 200,000. At least they would be, at the same time, earning their living and doing what they were put into the world to do. Still I just put that forward as a point of view that I am rather afraid of it.",
          "format": "text/plain",
          "purpose": "commenting"
        },
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "value": "Frank O'Connor",
          "format": "text/plain",
          "purpose": "tagging"
        },
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "value": "August 5 Panel Dicussion",
          "format": "text/plain",
          "purpose": "tagging"
        }
      ],
      "target": {
        "source": {
          "id": "https://tanyaclement.github.io/harvard1953/august-5-evening-part-two/canvas-1/canvas",
          "type": "Canvas",
          "partOf": [
            {
              "id": "https://tanyaclement.github.io/harvard1953/august-5-evening-part-two/manifest.json",
              "type": "Manifest"
            }
          ]
        },
        "selector": {
          "type": "PointSelector",
          "t": "600.0"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "@context": "http://www.w3.org/ns/anno.jsonld",
      "id": "august-5-evening-part-two-canvas-1-frank-o-connor-annotation-15.json",
      "type": "Annotation",
      "motivation": [
        "supplementing",
        "commenting"
      ],
      "body": [
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "value": " I want a representative audience. I mean, there is an enormous distinction between autocracy and any form of elective democracy. I think democracy was functioning in the 19th century, although the franchise was exceedingly limited. And in some ways in England, you got a superior type of politician when the franchise was so limited, merely because he didn't have to have the same demagogic appeal.",
          "format": "text/plain",
          "purpose": "commenting"
        },
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "value": "Frank O'Connor",
          "format": "text/plain",
          "purpose": "tagging"
        },
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "value": "August 5 Panel Dicussion",
          "format": "text/plain",
          "purpose": "tagging"
        }
      ],
